<br>
A Earth Elemental summoned with a focus object get extra strength, agility and other stats to help them dodge a little better and hit for higher damages.<br>
(Not a higher max but your pet should be hitting for max more often if its focused).<br>
<br>
A Water Elemental summoned with a focus object obtains the same number of hit points as an earth elemental of the same level summoned with no focus object. They also receive boosted stats<br>
 <br>
An Air Elemental summoned with a focus object gets a hit point bonus making it have approximately the same hit points as a water elemental summoned without a focus object of the same level. They receive less statistical bonus than the water elemental.<br>
<br>
A Fire Elemental summoned with a focus object gets a hit point bonus making it have approximately the same hit points as a air elemental summoned without a focus object of the same level. They receive around the same statistical bonuses as the air elemental.<br>
<br>
The best way I know of to see the difference is fighting HG's with Earth Pets.  Start with a level 39 unfocused (word?) pet and then after chaining through try doing it again with focused pet.  You should see a large difference in how long your pets last focused v unfocused.  <br>
